screen( "Disk Drivers" )
System Variables for Disk Drivers
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#hdv_bpb\#      = $472  ;L   vector    BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Getbpb\#
\#hdv_rw\#       = $476  ;L   vector    BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Rwabs\#
\#hdv_boot\#     = $47A  ;L   vector    Boot    Load boot sector
\#hdv_mediach\#  = $47E  ;L   vector    BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Mediach\#

\#flock\#        = $43E  ;W   control   DMA     0 = disable DMA
\#seekrate\#     = $440  ;W   data      Floppy
_fverify     = $444  ;W   control   Floppy  !0 = read after write
\#_nflops\#      = $4A6  ;W   control   BIOS    number floppy drives
\#_hz_200\#      = $4BA  ;L   data      BIOS    200 Hz system clock count
\#_drvbits\#     = $4C2  ;L   control   BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Drvmap\#
\#pun_ptr\#      = $516  ;L   address   AHDI    hd driver data

All disk I/O operations go through the above jump vectors.
Timeout tests should use the 200 Hz clock counter.
The drive map indicates which drives (A-Z) are active.
'_nflops' indicates whether drive 'B' is real or simulated.
\end

screen( "Device Drivers" )
System Variables for Device Drivers
----------------------------------------------------------------------
\#bconstat_vec\# = $51E  ;8L  vectors   BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Bconstat\# 0-7
\#bconin_vec\#   = $53E  ;8L  vectors   BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Bconin\#   0-7
\#bcostat_vec\#  = $55E  ;8L  vectors   BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Bcostat\#  0-7
\#bconout_vec\#  = $57E  ;8L  vectors   BIOS    \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Bconout\#  0-7

\#conterm\#      = $484  ;B   control   BIOS    CON: driver options
\#_hz_200\#      = $4BA  ;L   data      BIOS    200 Hz system clock count

All device I/O operations go through the above jump vectors.
Timeout tests should use the 200 Hz clock counter.

On the TT, another table jump vectors is used for all device numbers
above 5 (see \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Bconmap\#).  Device 1 is mapped to one of these extra
drivers, and \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Rsconf\# and \link("%%GLOBAL%%")Iorec\#(0) operate on the currently mapped
driver.
\end

